ECE 444.course_description:
This course studies computer network security by covering topics such as fundamental cryptographic algorithms; protocol design and analysis
for secure communications over Internet; efficient key management infrastructure; strong password protection; attack and security models;
practical security protocols in application layer, transport layer, network layer, and link layer. Students registering for ECE 543 are required to complete additional projects in advanced areas.
